However, the effect is not uniform throughout Europe.

Cities with limited supply and high demographic pressure continue to show notable resilience. The scarcity of available housing continues to act as a support for prices in numerous markets, limiting the impact of a possible slowdown in demand.

On the other hand, the most attentive investors observe how these periods of adjustment generate new entry opportunities. Historically, moments of financial uncertainty have made it possible to identify projects with more attractive valuations and access conditions that rarely appear during the more expansive phases of the cycle.

The key once again lies in information.

In an environment where the cost of financing changes rapidly and where each local market evolves differently, understanding the fundamental metrics of each opportunity becomes increasingly important in order to separate temporary trends from structural changes.

